video.title: Good Luck Charlie
video.synopsis: Tiny Charlotte "Charlie" Duncan looks to her parents and three older siblings, who do their best to give her advice about growing up.

episodes.synopsis: When Bob injures himself and PJ has to take him to the hospital, Teddy and the cute boy she's studying with have to watch Charlie all by themselves.
episodes.title: Study Date

episodes.synopsis: When PJ takes Charlie to the park, he flirts with a cute girl and accidentally brings home the wrong stroller -- and the wrong baby.
episodes.title: Baby Come Back

episodes.synopsis: Gabe and PJ think that Mrs. Dabney killed her husband, so they investigate. Meanwhile, Teddy is annoyed that Ivy has become texting buddies with Amy.
episodes.title: The Curious Case of Mr. Dabney

episodes.synopsis: Amy reveals that she was the high school mascot and pressures Teddy into trying out. Teddy tries to blow the audition, but gets the role anyway.
episodes.title: Double Whammy

episodes.synopsis: Teddy and Spencer double-date with Ivy and Emmett at the school dance, where the boys wind up in a dance-off that has them ignoring the girls.
episodes.title: Dance Off

episodes.synopsis: When Charlie sets off the shoplifting alarm at the local Redi-Mart, the manager puts Charlie and Teddy in holding -- and now Gabe must bust them out.
episodes.title: Charlie Did It!

episodes.synopsis: Teddy's scheme to get permission to go to a midnight movie is thwarted when she accidentally butt-dials Amy from her new phone.
episodes.title: Butt-Dialing Duncans

episodes.synopsis: It's Charlie's first birthday and the family reminisces about the day she was born and everyone had to find a way to get to the hospital.
episodes.title: Charlie Is 1

episodes.synopsis: When Bob decides to cut down the tree that holds Teddy and PJ's childhood treehouse, the kids stage a sit-in to protest.
episodes.title: Up a Tree

episodes.synopsis: When Teddy discovers that she has a great uncle that she's never heard about, she and Ivy visit him and take him to a baseball game.
episodes.title: Take Mel Out to the Ball Game

episodes.synopsis: PJ gets a job delivering food for Kwikki Chikki and falls in love with a customer, and Gabe has trouble with an unusual bully at school.
episodes.title: Boys Meet Girls

episodes.synopsis: Mrs. Dabney pays Teddy to watch her beloved cat while she goes out of town, and Gabe tells a whopper of a lie to impress a girl.
episodes.title: Kit and Kaboodle

episodes.synopsis: In an effort to win over her English teacher, Teddy brings Charlie to class and dresses her up in various adorable costumes for a presentation.
episodes.title: Teddy's Little Helper

episodes.synopsis: When Charlie loses her favorite blankie, Teddy tries to retrieve it from the donation truck, and PJ gets locked out of the house with Charlie inside.
episodes.title: Blankie Go Bye-Bye

episodes.synopsis: PJ makes a video of Charlie farting, which becomes an Internet sensation. Meanwhile, Teddy meets Spencer's parents and loves everything about them.
episodes.title: Charlie Goes Viral

episodes.synopsis: Spencer agrees to do a dance routine with Teddy for a talent show, but when he realizes what a bad dancer she is, he tries to get out of it.
episodes.title: Duncans Got Talent

episodes.synopsis: Teddy takes a job walking dogs to earn some extra money, but when she stops by Kwikki Chikki, she winds up stealing PJ's role as the new model.
episodes.title: Kwikki Chick

episodes.synopsis: Gabe is left in charge of Charlie while working on a school project with his nemesis, Jo. Meanwhile, Teddy must trick PJ into going to the dentist.
episodes.title: Charlie in Charge

episodes.synopsis: Teddy prepares to try out for the school play, but things go wrong when Charlie uses ink to draw all over her face right before the audition.
episodes.title: Sleepless in Denver

episodes.synopsis: Worried that Charlie is affecting her relationship with Spencer, Teddy decides to surprise Spencer at work -- only to discover him with another girl.
episodes.title: Girl Bites Dog

episodes.synopsis: Teddy is having a hard time recovering from her breakup with Spencer, so Ivy brings Skyler, the other girl, over to commiserate.
episodes.title: Teddy's Broken Heart Club Band

episodes.synopsis: When Teddy finds out that Spencer is seeing someone new, she lies and says that she too is seeing someone: a boy named Austin.
episodes.title: Teddy Rebounds

episodes.synopsis: Charlie develops a new bad habit of pushing buttons. Meanwhile, Teddy has to shoot a scene of an important moment in her life for film class.
episodes.title: Pushing Buttons

episodes.synopsis: On the family ski trip, Teddy meets a psychic who tells her she will come face-to-face with the love of her life during the vacation.
episodes.title: Snow Show: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Teddy, confused about who the love of her life could be, has Ivy meet her at the ski resort. Meanwhile, Gabe and PJ enter an ice skating competition.
episodes.title: Snow Show: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Bob is being unfairly stubborn and won't let his little girl practice driving, so Teddy goes behind his back and offers to drive Mrs. Dabney around.
episodes.title: Driving Mrs. Dabney

episodes.synopsis: Teddy, Gabe and Charlie try to sneak into the Gurgles concert. Meanwhile, Bob gets a miniature horse for Charlie's birthday party.
episodes.title: Charlie Is 2!

episodes.synopsis: Teddy takes a miserable job working at an ocean-themed children's party place in order to pay off her cell phone bill.
episodes.title: Something's Fishy

episodes.synopsis: Amy desperately tries to potty train Charlie in advance of her big interview with an exclusive preschool, but Charlie only likes to flush her toys.
episodes.title: Let's Potty

episodes.synopsis: Teddy and Ivy use a "fake phone call" app to convince Amy and Mary Lou that the other one gave permission for the girls to go to a party.
episodes.title: Appy Days

episodes.synopsis: When Bob and Amy plan to go away for a night, Teddy and PJ decide to throw a party -- but the party is compromised when Bob and Amy get into a fight.
episodes.title: Duncan Vs. Duncan

episodes.synopsis: Teddy has to bring Charlie along on a date with a boy she likes. When it turns out the boy is into role-playing, Teddy and Charlie have to play along.
episodes.title: A L.A.R.P. in the Park

episodes.synopsis: Teddy and Skyler decide to compete against PJ and Emmett in a battle of the bands competition, but PJ and Skyler end up falling for each other.
episodes.title: Battle of the Bands

episodes.synopsis: Amy plans a big musical song and dance performance for the annual hospital charity gala and tries to get the rest of the family to perform with her.
episodes.title: The Singin' Dancin' Duncans

episodes.synopsis: Teddy is having a hard time in class with Mr. Piper, who gives her a poor grade for not filling in test ovals correctly.
episodes.title: Teddy's Bear

episodes.synopsis: Gabe blackmails Teddy and PJ to pose as his parents in order to get him out of trouble with his teacher -- but the plan soon backfires.
episodes.title: Meet the Parents

episodes.synopsis: Gabe promises to be good for a whole week so that Amy and Bob will throw him a birthday party, but a huge snowstorm threatens their plans.
episodes.title: Gabe's 12-1/2 Birthday

episodes.synopsis: Teddy is losing interest in Derek, but she has a hard time breaking up with him because he keeps doing really nice things for her.
episodes.title: The Break Up

episodes.synopsis: When Teddy, Amy and Charlie travel to Chicago, they wind up at the set of "Shake It Up Chicago," where everyone thinks they are a famous hip-hop duo.
episodes.title: Charlie Shakes It Up

episodes.synopsis: Teddy joins the news team at school and finds out that the best story will be submitted for an internship with the local news.
episodes.title: Baby's New Shoes

episodes.synopsis: Teddy's laptop gets accidentally ruined and all her video diaries are gone.
episodes.title: Bye Bye Video Diary

episodes.synopsis: While baby-sitting for the new neighbors, Ivy convinces Teddy to try on some of the mom's earrings.
episodes.title: Monkey Business

episodes.synopsis: Teddy tries an at-home spray-on tanner, but when Charlie plays with the timer, Teddy ends up quite a few shades darker than intended.
episodes.title: P.J. in the City

episodes.synopsis: While on vacation in Hawaii, Amy steps into a forbidden garden and is told she has brought a curse on the family.
episodes.title: Sun Show: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Teddy anxiously searches for Charlie after she wandered away during their family vacation in Hawaii.
episodes.title: Sun Show: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: When Teddy buys a used car from Ivy's dad, it gets wrecked almost immediately.  Amy's upset when Charlie goes to her first day of preschool.
episodes.title: Amazing Gracie

episodes.synopsis: Teddy agrees to go with Bob to the Exterminator convention in hopes that she can make him happy enough that he'll agree to help her buy a new car.
episodes.title: Termite Queen

episodes.synopsis: Gabe and his friend Leo start a lemonade stand, but when they start to fight, they separate and wind up in an intense competition.
episodes.title: The Bob Duncan Experience

episodes.synopsis: When Teddy finds out she has a reputation for being a goody-two-shoes at school, she ditches for a day with Ivy in order to prove she can be bad, too.
episodes.title: Ditch Day

episodes.synopsis: Teddy convinces Mary Lou to audition to sing the national anthem at a Denver Nuggets basketball game, and Mary Lou wins.
episodes.title: Alley Oops

episodes.synopsis: Teddy and Ivy take Charlie trick or treating for Halloween. But when a neighborhood kid sets up a series of pranks, they plot revenge.
episodes.title: Scary Had a Little Lamb

episodes.synopsis: While on a family trip to Super Adventure Land, Gabe and Amy are approached about being in a commercial for the park.
episodes.title: Return to Super Adventure Land

episodes.synopsis: It's a special episode of "Good Luck Charlie" in which secrets are revealed!
episodes.title: Can You Keep a Secret?

episodes.synopsis: When Teddy and Amy discover that a mom at Charlie's book club is a book publisher, they each try to prove that they could write the next big hit.
episodes.title: Story Time

episodes.synopsis: This year, Amy finally gets to stay home and cook Thanksgiving dinner, but Bob worries that the food won't be edible.
episodes.title: It's a Charlie Duncan Thanksgiving

episodes.synopsis: Amy and Bob try to investigate where Charlie learned a bad word.
episodes.title: Teddy on Ice

episodes.synopsis: The Duncans plan to move to make room for the new baby.
episodes.title: Make Room for a Baby

episodes.synopsis: The basketball team has been on a losing streak and everyone thinks Teddy is the jinx.
episodes.title: Bad Luck Teddy

episodes.synopsis: Amy has Mary Lou throw her a baby shower and invites people who will give good gifts.
episodes.title: Amy Needs a Shower

episodes.synopsis: Amy wants Teddy to wear her old dress to prom, much to Teddy's chagrin.
episodes.title: Dress Mess

episodes.synopsis: Teddy and Spencer hide a secret from Amy: a production of her favorite musical.
episodes.title: Catch Me If You Can

episodes.synopsis: Bob and Amy have everyone in the family start weighing in with baby name options.
episodes.title: Name That Baby

episodes.synopsis: Amy tries to avoid giving birth to the new baby on Charlie's birthday.
episodes.title: Special Delivery: Pt. 1

episodes.synopsis: The newest Duncan is born!
episodes.title: Special Delivery: Pt. 2

episodes.synopsis: Amy brings home the baby and Bob's mom shows up to help, but unfortunately, drives everyone crazy!
episodes.title: Welcome Home

episodes.synopsis: The Duncan's take a quick trip to Dead Man's Lake, which ends up being more than they bargained for.
episodes.title: Baby's First Vacation

episodes.synopsis: At Teddy's encouragement, Harry Wentz decides to follow his dreams and open up a new restaurant.
episodes.title: Wentz's Weather Girl

episodes.synopsis: PJ and Emmett get an apartment together, but Amy is not prepared for PJ to leave the nest.
episodes.title: Baby Steps

episodes.synopsis: When Teddy joins the volleyball team, she realizes she is not very good and is too nice of a player.
episodes.title: T-Wrecks

episodes.synopsis: Amy's maternity leave is up, so the rest of the Duncan family is left to watch Toby and Charlie.
episodes.title: Teddy and the Bambino

episodes.synopsis: Amy volunteers to be "team mom" for Teddy's volleyball team and has the girls over for a sleepover.
episodes.title: Team Mom

episodes.synopsis: For Halloween, Amy dresses up like a Kangaroo, while Bob goes in his exterminator uniform.
episodes.title: Le Halloween

episodes.synopsis: Bob tries to help Spencer out of a fight with Teddy by advising him how to "handle" a Duncan woman.
episodes.title: Guys & Dolls

episodes.synopsis: Amy gets a part time nursing job at Gabe's school just as Gabe is getting in with the cool clique.
episodes.title: Nurse Blankenhooper

episodes.synopsis: After convincing Ivy to cast Charlie in the community play, Teddy cannot get Charlie to perform.
episodes.title: The Charlie Whisperer

episodes.synopsis: PJ starts reading Charlie a new book and finds himself obsessed with finishing it.
episodes.title: Study Buddy

episodes.synopsis: Teddy has been assigned the task of taking Charlie to see Santa at Super Adventure Land.
episodes.title: A Duncan Christmas

episodes.synopsis: Spencer gets the opportunity to start college in Boston early, and Teddy encourages him to go.
episodes.title: All Fall Down: Pt. 1

episodes.synopsis: The rare termites that Bob brought home escape into the house.
episodes.title: All Fall Down: Pt. 2

episodes.synopsis: After their house is destroyed by termites, the Duncans have to stay at a hotel, where Gabe attends a seminar and Teddy has a dream about the Muppets.
episodes.title: Duncan Dream House

episodes.synopsis: Teddy realizes it's time to move on and starts dating a new guy -- who looks remarkably like Spencer. PJ begins his first day at culinary school.
episodes.title: Doppel Date

episodes.synopsis: Gabe has a crush on the new neighbor, Lauren, until he discovers something about her family. Amy decides to film Teddy's Yale University interview.
episodes.title: Demolition Dabney

episodes.synopsis: Teddy wants to join Kelsey on the cheerleading squad after learning the competition will be in Hawaii. Bob tries to outsmart Charlie's preschool.
episodes.title: Go Teddy!

episodes.synopsis: Teddy is having a hard time with the essay portion of her college applications. An old classmate of Gabe's goes to him for advice about a prank.
episodes.title: Rock Enroll

episodes.synopsis: Teddy starts receiving anonymous threats. Amy and a fellow mom argue about who is responsible for teaching rude language to their daughters.
episodes.title: The Unusual Suspects

episodes.synopsis: Teddy throws a slumber party to help herself forget about her anniversary with Spencer, while PJ and Emmett take care of their neighbor's pet rat.
episodes.title: Rat-A-Teddy

episodes.synopsis: Charlie is not excited about sharing her birthday celebration. Teddy helps Beau break up with his girlfriend. Gabe gets a new reputation at school.
episodes.title: Charlie 4, Toby 1

episodes.synopsis: In the future, 14-year-old Charlie tries to apply some of Teddy's advice when Toby starts giving Charlie the silent treatment.
episodes.title: Futuredrama

episodes.synopsis: Beau convinces Teddy to go with him to a country-Western hangout. Meanwhile, Bob and Amy are out on a date, too -- are are in for a surprise.
episodes.title: Teddy's New Beau

episodes.synopsis: When Spencer shows up at Teddy's birthday party, she's forced to choose between him and Beau. Meanwhile, Bob accidentally buys Gabe a girl's shirt.
episodes.title: Teddy's Choice

episodes.synopsis: The family attends the Denver Pest Control Association's annual dance, where there's a heated competition between Amy and the woman Teddy can't stand.
episodes.title: Bug Prom

episodes.synopsis: Ivy tricks Teddy into joining her family on a road trip. Meanwhile, Amy is offended that Gabe didn't tell her he joined a baseball team.
episodes.title: Weekend in Vegas

episodes.synopsis: Teddy and her friends decide to go "Halloween caroling" to raise money for the school drama club. Gabe and PJ get spooked by PJ's creepy neighbor.
episodes.title: Fright Knight

episodes.synopsis: Teddy runs into Amy's younger sister, Jamie, and urges the fighting siblings to reconcile. A misunderstanding happens between PJ and a classmate.
episodes.title: Sister, Sister

episodes.synopsis: A job offer comes up in Tennesse that Beau just can't turn down. PJ and Emmett search for a new roommate to share the household expenses.
episodes.title: Bob's Beau-Be-Gone

episodes.synopsis: Teddy and PJ are visiting a college in New York City, where they get stuck in a blizzard and meet up with Jessie and the Ross kids.
episodes.title: Good Luck JESSIE: NYC Christmas

episodes.synopsis: Teddy is disappointed when she gets waitlisted at her first-choice college. Amy rides a scooter with Gabe, and Bob tells jokes at Charlie's school.
episodes.title: Accepted

episodes.synopsis: Gabe discovers PJ has been living in the backyard. Amy and Bob make a playdate with Charlie's friend and learn she's the daughter of a lesbian couple.
episodes.title: Down A Tree

episodes.synopsis: Teddy, who is ready to head off to college, has been having a hard time creating a final video diary for Charlie.
episodes.title: Goodbye Charlie: Pt. 1

episodes.synopsis: Amy and Bob are planning a very special going-away party for Teddy before she leaves for college.
episodes.title: Goodbye Charlie: Pt. 2
